=== Rails 2.1

- time zones
- timestamped migrations
- named_scope
- attribute changes
- partial updates
    -- validation problems!
- gem dependencies - config.gem
    -- gems:unpack
    -- gems:build (native)
    -- can unpack gems in vendor/plugins if it has an init.rb
- anonymous scopes
- has_one :through
- rake rails:update - scripts, javascript, config files?
- script plugin install with Git
- dbconsole
- Ruby 1.9 compatibility
- protect_from_forgery

  - MRI
- New Ruby VMs/Interpreters
  - YARV - all C
    - fork: Apple employee: MacRuby - Objective C
  - Rubinius - more Ruby, less C
  - MagLev/Gemstone - Smalltalk VM (commercial, closed source)
  - JRuby - Java VM
  - IronRuby - .NET

- Git!
  -- Git Internals PDF
  -- Linus Torvalds - presentation at Google about Git

- pluggable controller caching
  - http://ryandaigle.com/articles/2007/12/19/what-s-new-in-edge-rails-pluggable-controller-caching
  
- read only relationships: has_many :reports, :readonly => true
- Model.all, Model.first, Model.last

- labels: <%= f.label :title %>
          <%= label_tag 'name' %>
          
- turning sessions on and off in controllers: session: off

- routes recognition is re-implemented and faster (tree)

  